Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,[MUSIC PLAYING]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.45,0:00:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,[APPLAUSE]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.68,0:00:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,FRANK ABAGNALE: Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.89,0:00:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a pleasure to\Nbe here this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.76,0:00:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna ask your\Nindulgence on two things.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.61,0:00:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's allergy season, so\NI have a real hard time
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.21,0:00:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,during this time of\Nthe year speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.73,0:00:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And two, most of the speaking I\Ndo when I walk up to the podium
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.00,0:00:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is very technical.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.89,0:00:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It deals with cyber crime\Nand identity theft, forgery,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.08,0:00:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,embezzlements, and\Nthings of that nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.30,0:00:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't often talk\Nabout my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.95,0:00:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But Google has asked me today\Nto do something different
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.83,0:00:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and talk a little\Nbit about my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.46,0:00:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So I will do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.61,0:00:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And then at the end, of\Ncourse, I'll take questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.78,0:00:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And those questions can be\Nabout any subject matter
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.03,0:00:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that you like to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.49,0:00:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,As you know, I've had a lot\Nof people tell my story.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.26,0:00:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a great movie director\Nwrite a film about my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.64,0:00:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a great Broadway musical\Nteam make a Tony Award-winning
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.82,0:00:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Broadway musical about my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.53,0:00:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Had a popular\Ntelevision show on TV,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.39,0:01:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,"White Collar," for four\Nyears created around my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.11,0:01:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And most of those\Nvery creative people
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.00,0:01:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,have actually never\Nmet me personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.13,0:01:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But they've enjoyed telling my\Nstory from their point of view.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.50,0:01:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought I would take\Na few minutes this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.74,0:01:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and actually tell you the\Nstory from my point of view.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.79,0:01:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I was raised just north of\NNew York City in Westchester
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.58,0:01:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,County, New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.45,0:01:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I was actually one\Nof four children
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.40,0:01:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in the family, the so-called\Nmiddle child of the four.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.07,0:01:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I was educated there by the\NChristian Brothers of Ireland
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.01,0:01:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in a private Catholic\Nschool called
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.61,0:01:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Iona where I went to school from\Nkindergarten to high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.12,0:01:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,By the time I had reached the\Nage of 16, in the 10th grade,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.50,0:01:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,my parents after 22\Nyears of marriage one day
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.84,0:01:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,decided to get a divorce.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.11,0:01:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Unlike most divorces where\Nthe children were usually
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.28,0:01:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the first to know,\Nmy parents were
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.87,0:01:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,very good about\Nkeeping that a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.18,0:01:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember being in the 10th\Ngrade when the father walked
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.55,0:01:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,in the classroom one\Nafternoon, asked a brother
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.51,0:01:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to excuse me from class.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.76,0:01:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,When I came out in the hallway,\Nthe father handed me my books
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.58,0:01:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and told me that\None of the brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.08,0:01:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,would drive me to\Nthe county seat
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.55,0:02:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,in White Plains, New York\Nwhere I would meet my parents,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.43,0:02:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and they would explain\Nwhat was going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.81,0:02:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember the brother dropped\Nme at the steps of a big stone
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.35,0:02:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,building and told me\Nto go on up the steps
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.10,0:02:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,where my parents would be\Nwaiting for me in the lobby.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.36,0:02:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember climbing the steps,\Nseeing a sign on the building
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.86,0:02:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that said "Family Court."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.45,0:02:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But I really didn't\Nunderstand what that meant.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.81,0:02:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,When I arrived in the lobby,\Nmy parents were not there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.10,0:02:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was ushered into the\Nback of an immense courtroom
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.44,0:02:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,where my parents were\Nstanding before a judge.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.90,0:02:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't hear what the judge\Nwas saying, nor my parents'
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.42,0:02:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,response.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.89,0:02:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But eventually, the judge saw\Nme at the back of the room
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.29,0:02:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and motioned me to\Napproach the bench.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.57,0:02:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So I walked up the stand\Nin between my parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.21,0:02:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember distinctly that\Nthe judge never looked at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.09,0:02:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He never acknowledged\NI was standing there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.31,0:02:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He simply read from his papers\Nand said that my parents
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.10,0:02:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,were getting a divorce.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.67,0:02:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And because I was\N16 years of age,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.09,0:02:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I would need to\Ntell the court which
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.59,0:02:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,parent I chose to live with.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.08,0:02:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I started to cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.04,0:02:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So I turned and ran\Nout of the courtroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.71,0:02:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Judge called for a\N10-minute recess.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.48,0:03:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But by the time my parents\Ngot outside, I was gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.05,0:03:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother never saw me again\Nfor about seven years until I
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.93,0:03:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,was a young adult.\NContrary to the movie,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.06,0:03:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,my father never saw me or\Never spoke to me again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.11,0:03:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,In the mid-1960s, running\Naway was a very popular thing
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.90,0:03:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,for young people.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.65,0:03:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of them got caught up\Nin Haight-Ashbury, the hippie
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.05,0:03:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,scene, the drug scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.40,0:03:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, I took a few\Nbelongings from my home,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.32,0:03:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,packed them in a bag, boarded\Nwhat was then the New Haven
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.05,0:03:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and Hartford railroad\Nfor the short train ride
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.97,0:03:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,down to Grand Central\NTerminal in New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.85,0:03:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,My father did own a\Nstationary store in Manhattan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.37,0:03:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It was located on the\Ncorner of 40th and Madison.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.16,0:03:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Like all of us, we had\Nto work in that store.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.08,0:03:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So from the time I was\Nabout 13, I made deliveries
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.81,0:03:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,my dad in the summer on a bike.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.18,0:03:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew the city very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.50,0:03:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So naturally, I started looking\Nfor the same type of work.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.02,0:03:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There were a lot of signs\Non the windows-- stock
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.02,0:03:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,boy, delivery boy, part time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.24,0:03:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd walk in and apply.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.62,0:03:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So tell me, young\Nman, how old are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.39,0:03:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, 16.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.59,0:03:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,How far did you\Ngo in high school?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.11,0:03:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, 10th grade.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.38,0:03:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll hire you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.30,0:03:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to work for a\Nsmall amount of money
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.05,0:03:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,a few hours a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.82,0:04:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But I soon realized I\Ncouldn't support myself
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.28,0:04:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,on that amount of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.51,0:04:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I also realize as long as people\Nbelieved I was 16 years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.67,0:04:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,they weren't going to\Npay me any more money.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.28,0:04:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,At 16, I was 6 foot tall.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.90,0:04:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I've always had\Nlittle gray hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.64,0:04:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,My friends in school\Nused to say that once
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.50,0:04:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,a week, when we dressed\Nin a suit for mass,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.93,0:04:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I looked more like a teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.74,0:04:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So I decided to\Nlie about my age.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.41,0:04:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In New York, we had a\Ndriver's license at 16.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.20,0:04:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Back then, it didn't have a\Nphoto on it, just an IBM card.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.32,0:04:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So I altered one digit\Nof my date of birth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.69,0:04:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I was actually born\Nin April of 1948.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.11,0:04:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But I dropped the four,\Nconverted it to a three.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.57,0:04:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And that made me 26 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.18,0:04:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I walked around applying\Nfor the same type of work.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.61,0:04:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,People gave me a little more\Nmoney, a few more hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.52,0:04:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But even then, it was very\Ndifficult to make ends meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.57,0:04:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the few things I\Nhad taken when I left home
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.65,0:04:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,was a checkbook.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.49,0:04:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I had money from\Nwork in the summers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.46,0:04:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I had some money in\Nthat checking account.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.42,0:04:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So every so often, I\Nwould write a check
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.40,0:04:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to supplement my income--
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.84,0:04:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,$20, $25.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.09,0:04:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The funds were there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.96,0:05:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The checks were good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.34,0:05:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was my friends, my peers,\Nwho would constantly say to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.58,0:05:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, you're\Nthe only guy who
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.17,0:05:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,walks into a bank in\Nthe middle of Manhattan.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.73,0:05:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You have no account there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.23,0:05:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know a soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.42,0:05:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You talk to somebody behind the\Ndesk, and they OK your check.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.88,0:05:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, my checks are good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.13,0:05:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I walked in there,\Nthey wouldn't touch my check.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.90,0:05:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You walk in there,\Nthey don't bat an eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.75,0:05:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Years later, reporters\Nwould write and speculate
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.94,0:05:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and say that that was my\Nupbringing-- mannerisms, dress,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.58,0:05:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,appearance, speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.39,0:05:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever it was, it\Nwas very easy to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.16,0:05:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So consequently, when\Nthe money ran out,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.65,0:05:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I kept writing those checks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.37,0:05:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, the checks\Nstarted to bounce.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.04,0:05:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Police started looking\Nfor me as a runaway.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.01,0:05:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought maybe\Nit was a good time
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.55,0:05:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to start thinking about\Nleaving New York City.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.58,0:05:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was quite\Napprehensive about going
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.50,0:05:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to Chicago or Miami, wondered\Nif they'd cash a New York
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.53,0:05:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,check on a New York\Ndriver's license in Miami
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.56,0:05:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,as quickly as they\Ndid in Manhattan.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.93,0:05:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I was walking up 42nd Street\None afternoon about 5 o'clock
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.26,0:05:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in the evening, 16\Nyears old, pondering
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.87,0:06:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,all of these things,\Nwhen I started
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.58,0:06:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to approach the front door of an\Nold hotel that used to be there
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.05,0:06:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,called the Commodore Hotel--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.71,0:06:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,now the Grand Hyatt.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.21,0:06:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as I was about to get to\Nthe front door of the hotel,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.09,0:06:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,out stepped an Eastern Airline\Nflight crew onto the sidewalk.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.96,0:06:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't help but notice\Nthe captain, the copilot,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.22,0:06:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the flight engineer, about\Nthree or four flight attendants
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.64,0:06:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,dragging their bags to the\Ncurb to load them in the van
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.98,0:06:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to take them to the airport.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.87,0:06:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,As they loaded the van, I\Nthought to myself, that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.11,0:06:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I could pose as a pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.91,0:06:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I could travel all over\Nthe world for free.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.25,0:06:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I probably could get\Njust about anybody
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.65,0:06:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,anywhere to cash a check for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.62,0:06:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So I walked up the\Nstreet a little further
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.37,0:06:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to 42nd and Park.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.78,0:06:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to crossover.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.89,0:06:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard a huge helicopter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.78,0:06:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So I looked up, and there\Nwas New York Airways
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.79,0:06:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,landing on the roof of\Nthe Pan Am building.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.28,0:06:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Pan Am, the nation's\Nflag carrier, the airline
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.47,0:06:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that flew around the world--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.34,0:06:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, what a\Nperfect airline to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.67,0:06:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So the next day, I\Nplaced a phone call
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.41,0:06:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to the executive corporate\Noffices of Pan Am.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.32,0:06:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember distinctly when\Nthe phone was ringing,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.54,0:07:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I had absolutely no idea\Nwhat I was going to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.93,0:07:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,When they answered,\N"Pan American Airlines.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.73,0:07:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, can I help you?"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.26,0:07:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.82,0:07:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.39,0:07:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to speak to somebody\Nin the purchasing department.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.89,0:07:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,"Purchasing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.76,0:07:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,One moment."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.58,0:07:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The clerk came on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.41,0:07:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.90,0:07:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you can help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.82,0:07:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is John Black.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.65,0:07:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a copilot with a company\Nbased out of San Francisco.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.98,0:07:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Been with the company about\Nseven years, but never
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.53,0:07:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,had anything like\Nthis come up before.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.58,0:07:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,"What's the problem?"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.62,0:07:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we flew a trip\Nin here yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.63,0:07:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going out later today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.57,0:07:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday, I sent my uniform\Nout through the hotel
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.95,0:07:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to have it dry cleaned.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.42,0:07:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the hotel and the cleaners\Nsay they can't find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.27,0:07:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm with a flight in\Nabout four hours--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.34,0:07:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,new uniform.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.12,0:07:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,"Don't you have\Na spare uniform?"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.17,0:07:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly, back home\Nin San Francisco.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.20,0:07:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'd never get it here\Nin time for my flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.93,0:07:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you understand this will cost\Nyou the price of a uniform, not
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.72,0:07:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the company?"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.83,0:07:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.86,0:07:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,"Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.36,0:07:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be right back."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.56,0:07:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He came back and\Nsaid, my supervisor
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.33,0:07:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,says you need to go down\Nto the Well-Built Uniform
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.73,0:07:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Company on Fifth Avenue.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.99,0:07:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,They're our supplier.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.99,0:08:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll call them and let them\Nknow you're on the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.11,0:08:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's exactly\Nwhat I wanted to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.90,0:08:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So I went down to the\NWell-Built Uniform Company.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.98,0:08:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Little fella, Mr.\NRosen fitted me out
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.80,0:08:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in the uniform, black aberdeen\Nwith three gold stripes
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.35,0:08:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,on the arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.85,0:08:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I certainly looked old\Nenough to be the pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.00,0:08:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,When he was all done, I\Nsaid, how much do I owe you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.17,0:08:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,"Well, the uniform's $286."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.87,0:08:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.96,0:08:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll write you a check.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.32,0:08:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,"No, um, we can't\Ntake any checks."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.62,0:08:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, then I'll\Njust pay you cash.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.67,0:08:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't accept cash.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.87,0:08:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to fill out\Nthis computer card.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.76,0:08:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Then in these boxes, put\Nyour employee number.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.25,0:08:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we bill this back\Nunder uniform allowance,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.83,0:08:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,comes out of your\Nnext Pan Em paycheck.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.48,0:08:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's even better.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.62,0:08:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead and do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.11,0:08:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,New York had two airports--
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.43,0:08:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,LaGuardia and Kennedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.60,0:08:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,LaGuardia was 20 minutes from\NManhattan, Kennedy was 50.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.45,0:08:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally, LaGuardia being\Nthe closer of the two,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.76,0:08:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that's where I went.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.96,0:08:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I spent most of the morning\Nwalking around LaGuardia
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.30,0:08:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,in the uniform, trying\Nto figure out now
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.01,0:08:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that I had this\Nuniform, how the hell do
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.90,0:08:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you get on these planes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.13,0:08:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a little hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.05,0:09:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So about lunchtime, I\Nwalked in the luncheonette
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.16,0:09:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,in the terminal, sat down\Nat the counter on the stool
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.37,0:09:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and ordered a sandwich.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.84,0:09:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Moments later, a\NTWA crew walked in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.60,0:09:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The flight attendants\Nsat in the booth,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.22,0:09:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but the pilots up at the\Ncounter on either side of me,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.80,0:09:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and captain right next to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.54,0:09:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Now back before deregulation\Nof the airlines,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.12,0:09:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,airline people\Nthought of themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.77,0:09:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,as just one big family.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.57,0:09:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So they didn't hesitate a\Nmoment to talk to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.86,0:09:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The captain kinda leaned over.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.26,0:09:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,"Hey, young man.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.76,0:09:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,How's Pan Am doing?"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.11,0:09:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Doing just fine, captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.44,0:09:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,"Tell me, what's Pan Am\Ndoing out here at LaGuardia?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.61,0:09:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Pan Am doesn't fly\Ninto LaGuardia.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.30,0:09:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,They only fly into Kennedy."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.61,0:09:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I picked up\Non that right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.11,0:09:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we came into\NKennedy at a layover.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.11,0:09:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So I came over to\Nvisit some friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.65,0:09:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Matter of fact, I'm on my\Nway back to Kennedy now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.30,0:09:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,"So tell me, young man, what\Ntype of equipment are you on?"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.84,0:09:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Airline people have a\Nlot of jargon for things.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.18,0:09:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,One of them is they never call\Na plane a plane or an aircraft,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.16,0:09:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,they call it equipment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.28,0:09:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And what type of\Nequipment you're on meant
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.44,0:09:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,what type of plane do you fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.69,0:09:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Back then, a DC-8, a 707.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.05,0:09:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I didn't know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.30,0:10:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought,\Ntype of equipment?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.43,0:10:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The only equipment\NI'm on is this stool.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.81,0:10:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They must mean what\Ntype of equipment
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.35,0:10:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is on the planes I fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.88,0:10:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought, well, they got\Nthe wings, they got the engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.12,0:10:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They always had a\Nsticker on the engine
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.74,0:10:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,who manufactured the engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.14,0:10:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So I said, yeah, it's\NGeneral Electric.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.76,0:10:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All three pilots kind of just\Nstopped eating and leaned over.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.65,0:10:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And the captain\Nsaid, oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.02,0:10:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you fly,\Na washing machine?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.43,0:10:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So I knew I had said\Nthe wrong thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.97,0:10:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Out the door I went.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.79,0:10:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody had an\Nairline ID card,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.98,0:10:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,a plastic laminated card much\Nlike a driver's license today.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.18,0:10:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet without the ID card,\Nthe uniform was worthless.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.46,0:10:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I went back to Manhattan\Npretty discouraged
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.32,0:10:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking where would I come up\Nwith a Pan American Airlines
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.78,0:10:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,corporate ID?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.60,0:10:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sitting in the hotel room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.93,0:10:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I noticed a big thick\NManhattan Yellow Pages.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.02,0:10:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So I pulled them down on\Nthe bed, flipped them open,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.25,0:10:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and looked under the\Nword identification.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.01,0:10:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There were three or\Nfour pages of companies
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.90,0:10:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,who made convention badges,\Nmetal badges, plastic badges,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.90,0:10:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,police badges, fire badges.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.55,0:10:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Started to call around.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.54,0:10:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, one\Ncompany said, listen,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.94,0:10:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,most of those airline\NIDs manufactured
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.58,0:11:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,by Polaroid, 3M company.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.78,0:11:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to call one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.12,0:11:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally got the 3M company\Non the phone in Manhattan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.64,0:11:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,"Yeah, we manufacture Pan\NAm's identification system
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.33,0:11:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,along with a number\Nof other carriers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.61,0:11:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,How come?"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.53,0:11:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So I tell them, I'm a purchasing\Nofficer for a major US carrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.72,0:11:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm in New York\Njust for the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.33,0:11:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We're getting ready\Nto expand our routes,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.04,0:11:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,hire a lot of new employees,\Ngo to a formal ID.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.69,0:11:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We're very impressed\Nwith this Pan Am format.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.70,0:11:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Wondered if I came by your\Noffice this afternoon briefly,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.07,0:11:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,we could discuss\Nquantity and price.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.99,0:11:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,"By all means, come on by."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.58,0:11:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So I went by dressed in a suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.90,0:11:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And the sales rep\Nopened the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.32,0:11:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we do United,\NBraniff, National, Pan Am.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.22,0:11:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Pan Am!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.51,0:11:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We like this Pan Am format.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.59,0:11:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Wonder if you have a\Nsample I could bring back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.55,0:11:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, I'll be right back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.03,0:11:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And he brought me\Nback a 5" by 7"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.92,0:11:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,glossy piece of paper with a\Npicture of an ID card blown up
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.28,0:11:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in the middle of it, someone\Nelse's picture in the picture,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.34,0:11:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,John Doe for a name, and in\Nbold red ink across the front,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.83,0:11:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,"This is a sample only."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.49,0:11:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, no, I'm\Nafraid this won't do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.03,0:11:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to bring back an\Nactual physical card.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.29,0:12:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And by the way, what is all\Nthis equipment on the floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.33,0:12:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,"We don't just sell these cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.66,0:12:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We sell the system--\Ncamera, laminator."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.96,0:12:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to buy all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.41,0:12:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,"Absolutely."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.34,0:12:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But tell you what, since we\Nhave to buy it all, why don't we
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.17,0:12:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,just demonstrate how\Nit works and use me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.03,0:12:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,"Fine, have a seat right here."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.39,0:12:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Took my picture,\Nand made the card.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.13,0:12:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,[LAUGHTER]
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.28,0:12:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going down the\Nelevator studying the card.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.32,0:12:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It had a blue border\Nacross the top,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.25,0:12:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,about a half inch in\NPan Am's color blue,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.42,0:12:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,but not a single thing\Non the card said Pan-Am--
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.98,0:12:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,no logo, no insignia,\Nno company name.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.31,0:12:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This was a plastic card\Nlike a credit card.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.32,0:12:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So you couldn't type on\Nit, couldn't write on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.36,0:12:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,couldn't print on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.80,0:12:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Discouraged, I put it in\Nmy pocket, headed back
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.11,0:12:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.50,0:12:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,As I was walking back, I noticed\Nthat I'd passed a hobby shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.46,0:12:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So I turned around\Nand walked back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.19,0:12:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, sir, I see you\Nsell a lot of models here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.36,0:12:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you sell models of\Ncommercial jetliners?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.85,0:12:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,"Sure, over there."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.92,0:12:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And I bought a model of\Na Pan Am 707 cargo jet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.27,0:12:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Took it back to my\Nroom, opened the box,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.94,0:12:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,threw all the parts out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.96,0:12:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But they're at the\Nbottom of the box
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.46,0:12:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,was a sheet of decals\Nthat went on the model.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.47,0:13:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And when soaked in\Na glass of water,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.04,0:13:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the little Pan Am\Nblue globe that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.56,0:13:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,went on the tail of\Nthe plastic plane
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.90,0:13:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,went perfect up at the\Ntop of the plastic card.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.47,0:13:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And the word "Pan Am"\Nand the special styling
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.34,0:13:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and graphics that would\Nhave went on the fuselage
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.38,0:13:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,went perfect across\Nthe top of the card.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.37,0:13:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And the clear decal on\Nthe laminated plastic
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.79,0:13:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,made a beautiful\Nidentification card.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.18,0:13:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Pan Am says they estimate that\Nbetween the ages of 16 and 18,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.72,0:13:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I flew more than a\Nmillion miles for free,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.12,0:13:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,boarded more than 260 commercial\Naircraft in more than 26
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.99,0:13:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,countries around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.48,0:13:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Pan Am says, keep in mind the\Nfact that Frank Abagnale did
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.50,0:13:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,in fact pose as\None of our pilots
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.08,0:13:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,for a long period of time,\Nhe never once stepped
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.87,0:13:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,on board one of our aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.09,0:13:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.23,0:13:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I never flew on Pan\NAm because I was
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.75,0:13:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,afraid someone might\Nsay to me, "You know,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.50,0:13:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm based in San Francisco.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.85,0:13:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Been out there 16 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.62,0:13:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't recall ever\Nmeeting you before."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.35,0:13:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Or someone might say,\Nyou know, "Your ID card
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.22,0:13:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is not exactly like my ID card."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.16,0:13:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead, I flew\Non everyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.80,0:13:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If I wanted to go\Nsomewhere, I literally just
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.35,0:14:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,walked out to the\Nairport, walked up
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.36,0:14:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,on the board, United\NFlight 800 to Chicago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.30,0:14:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I went downstairs to the\Ndoor marked United operations
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.78,0:14:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and walked in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.95,0:14:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The operations clerk, "Hey, Pan\NAm, what can we do for you?"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.08,0:14:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I was wondering\Nif the jumpseat's
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.45,0:14:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,open on 800 [INAUDIBLE] Chicago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.31,0:14:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I was open this evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.31,0:14:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Like to get a pink slip pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.04,0:14:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd give them my ID,\Nwrite me out a pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.81,0:14:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd walk out, hand it\Nto the flight attendant.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.73,0:14:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,She'd open the door\Nto the cockpit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.59,0:14:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'd step in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.28,0:14:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They had a captain, a copilot,\Na flight engineer, and the seat
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.86,0:14:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,behind the captain called\Nthe jumpseat pilots dead head
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.68,0:14:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,on company time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.33,0:14:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Because pilots\Nlove to talk shop,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.43,0:14:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,once you picked\Nup that jargon, it
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.02,0:14:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,was the same conversation\Nover and over and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.32,0:14:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just step on board.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.43,0:14:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Even [? John ?] Bob Davis\Nbe running to Chicago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.43,0:14:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,On the taxi out, always\Nthe same questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.66,0:14:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,"So Bob, how long you\Nbeen with Pan Am?"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.64,0:14:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Been flying about seven years.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.14,0:14:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,"What position you fly?"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.49,0:14:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Right seat, which is airline\Nterminology for a copilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.91,0:14:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,"What type of\Nequipment are you on?"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.53,0:14:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Had that one down perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.28,0:14:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,[LAUGHTER]
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.59,0:14:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Matter of fact, whatever\Nthey flew, I didn't fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.80,0:14:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So I had no problems with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.80,0:15:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we'd arrive in Chicago,\NI'd go by the Pan Am ticket
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.46,0:15:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,counter, but just enough to get\Nthe attention of the passenger
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.15,0:15:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,service rep.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.91,0:15:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, I haven't laid\Nover here in over a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.49,0:15:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We're still at the--
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.37,0:15:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,"Palmer House Hilton downtown.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.62,0:15:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Catch a crew bus lower\Nlevel door three, out."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.64,0:15:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I go down to the Palmer\NHouse Hilton, walk in,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.64,0:15:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and on the corner\Nof the registration
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.29,0:15:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,desk was a little sign\Nthat said "Airline crews."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.29,0:15:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a three-ring binder.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.50,0:15:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You signed in, referenced your\Nflight number, showed your ID.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.23,0:15:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd give me a key.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.14,0:15:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd stay two or three\Ndays, and Pan Am
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.01,0:15:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,would be direct billed\Nfor my room and my meals.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.99,0:15:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I also could cash a personal\Ncheck at the front desk
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.35,0:15:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,because I was an\Nemployee of the airline.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.85,0:15:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The airline had a\Ncontract with the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.60,0:15:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And as a courtesy,\Nthey'd cash your check.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.78,0:15:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But then I found out\Nthat every airline
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.61,0:15:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,honors every other airline\Nemployee's personal check.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.46,0:15:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, a reciprocal agreement\Nstill practiced today in 2017.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.93,0:15:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So at the San Francisco airport,\Na Delta flight attendant
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.54,0:15:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,can walk up to an American\NAirlines ticket counter,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.83,0:15:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,show her ID, and cash a\Npersonal check up to $100
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.27,0:15:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and vice versa.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.80,0:15:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, when I found that\Nout, I'd go out to JFK or LAX.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.98,0:15:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Only, I'd go to everybody--
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.15,0:16:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Northeast, National,\NKLM, Air France.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.83,0:16:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It would take me a good eight\Nhours stopping at every counter
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.37,0:16:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,in every building.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.20,0:16:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,By the time I got all the\Nway around the other end
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.28,0:16:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of the airport, at least\Neight hours had gone by.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.28,0:16:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you have\Nin eight hours?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.66,0:16:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Shift change, new people.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.74,0:16:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'd go all the way back\Naround the other way again.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.05,0:16:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,As you know, I went\Non to impersonate
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.03,0:16:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,a doctor in a Georgia\Nhospital for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.55,0:16:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I took the bar exams in\NLouisiana, passed the bar,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.45,0:16:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,went to work for\NAttorney General PF
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.28,0:16:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Gremillion in the civil\Ndivision of the state court
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.40,0:16:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,where I spent about a\Nyear practicing law.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.59,0:16:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,In both the job as the\Nlawyer and the doctor,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.95,0:16:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,no one ever doubted\Nfor a second I was not
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.17,0:16:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,eligible or qualified to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.51,0:16:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I on my own resigned\Nand moved on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.96,0:16:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, like any\Ncriminal, sooner or later,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.88,0:16:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,you get caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.83,0:16:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was no exception\Nto that rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.64,0:16:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I was actually arrested\Njust once in my life
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.04,0:16:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,when I was 21 years old\Nby the French police
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.59,0:16:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,in a small town in southern\NFrance called Montpellier.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.19,0:16:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The French police were\Nactually arresting me
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.02,0:16:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,on an Interpol warrant issued\Nby the Swedish police who
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.93,0:16:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,were looking for me\Nfor forgery in Sweden,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.91,0:17:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but believed that I\Nwas living in France.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.32,0:17:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,When the French authorities\Ntook me into custody
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.32,0:17:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,on that warrant, they\Nrealized I had forged checks
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.75,0:17:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,all over France.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.66,0:17:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So they refused to honor the\Nwarrant and Sweden's request
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.47,0:17:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,for my extradition.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.03,0:17:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,They later convicted\Nme of forgery
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.77,0:17:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and sent me to French prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.90,0:17:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I served my time\Nat a place called
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.34,0:17:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the maison d'arret,\Nthe house of arrest,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.14,0:17:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,in a small town in southern\NFrance called Perpignan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.01,0:17:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Steven Spielberg\Ntold Barbara Walters,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.09,0:17:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,"It was extremely important\Nto me to go back to that cell,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.75,0:17:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to the exact cell he was\Nin and reconstruct it
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.25,0:17:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,according to the logbooks\Nduring his stay there."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.10,0:17:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, "To my\Namazement, there was
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.60,0:17:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,a blanket on the floor, no\Nmattress, a hole in the floor
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.24,0:17:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to go the bathroom, no\Nplumbing, no electricity."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.99,0:17:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, "According\Nto the log books,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.37,0:17:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I entered the prison\Nat 198 pounds,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.13,0:17:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,left the prison at 109 pounds."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.95,0:17:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,When my sentence\Nwas over in France,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.64,0:17:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I was extradited to\NSweden where I was later
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.91,0:17:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,convicted of forgery in\Na Swedish court of law
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.67,0:17:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and sent to a Swedish\Npenitentiary in Malmo, Sweden.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.48,0:18:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,When my prison term\Nwas up in Sweden,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.28,0:18:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,US federal authorities\Ntook custody of me
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.29,0:18:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and returned me to\Nthe United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.21,0:18:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, United\NStates federal judge
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.52,0:18:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,in Atlanta, Georgia, which\Nsentenced me to 12 years
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.18,0:18:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,in federal prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.77,0:18:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I served 4 of the 12\Nyears at a federal prison
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.59,0:18:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,in Petersburg, Virginia.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.45,0:18:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was 26 years\Nold, the government
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.28,0:18:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,offered to take me out of\Nprison on the condition
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.77,0:18:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I go to work with an agency\Nof the federal government
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.02,0:18:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,for the remainder of my\Nsentence until my parole had
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.23,0:18:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,been satisfactorily completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.45,0:18:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I agreed and was released.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.03,0:18:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This year, I'm celebrating\N41 years at the FBI.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.27,0:18:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been at the Bureau\Nfor more than four decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.25,0:18:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I work out of Washington DC.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.41,0:18:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I actually make my home in\NCharleston, South Carolina.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.44,0:18:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So every Monday, I\Nfly up to Washington,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.35,0:18:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,about an hour flight, and I\Ngo home on Thursday evenings.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.86,0:18:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I live in Charleston with my one\Nand only wife of 40 plus years
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.98,0:18:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and my three sons.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.65,0:18:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,My youngest boy graduated\Nfrom the University of Beijing
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.20,0:18:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in China.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.71,0:18:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He went on to get his\Nmaster's degree there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.54,0:19:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He reads, writes, and\Nspeaks Chinese fluently.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.21,0:19:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He works for a San\NFrancisco gaming
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.01,0:19:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,company called Glu Mobile.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.45,0:19:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,He designs games for\Nthe Chinese market.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.99,0:19:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All of his games are\Nin Chinese, and they're
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.88,0:19:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in their fourth generation\Nas mobile games and devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.63,0:19:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,My middle son graduated\Nfrom University of Nevada
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.67,0:19:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in Las Vegas.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.42,0:19:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,His degree was in business.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.65,0:19:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He and his wife\Ngraduated together.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.78,0:19:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And he and her own a\Nbusiness in South Carolina,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.36,0:19:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and they manage that\Nbusiness together.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.67,0:19:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,My oldest son graduated from\NUniversity of Kansas at KU.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.71,0:19:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We went on to\NLoyola School of Law
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.14,0:19:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,in Chicago to get\Nhis law degree.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.58,0:19:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Passed the bar in\NIllinois, and went on
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.20,0:19:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to make his dad\Nvery, very proud.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.70,0:19:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He's an FBI agent.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.35,0:19:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He's been in the\NBureau about 12 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.09,0:19:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,He supervises a team that\Ndeals with American citizens
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.91,0:19:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,kidnapped overseas.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.17,0:19:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So they're a response\Nteam that operates out
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.42,0:19:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of Quantico, Virginia.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.79,0:19:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,As many of you know, I had very\Nlittle to do with the film.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.27,0:19:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I would have preferred not to\Nhad a movie made about my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.85,0:19:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I actually raised my three\Nboys in Tulsa, Oklahoma
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.95,0:19:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,in the same house for 25 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.37,0:20:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,My neighbors had\Nno idea who I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.58,0:20:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And I would have preferred\Nit stayed that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.50,0:20:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But Steven Spielberg\Ntold Barbara Walters
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.69,0:20:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,he felt compelled to tell\Nthe world the story not
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.93,0:20:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,because of what I did,\Nbut because of what
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.94,0:20:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd done my life after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.82,0:20:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He loved the redemption\Nside of the story,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.16,0:20:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,wanted the world\Nto know the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.48,0:20:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the end, my family\Nand I were very pleased
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.48,0:20:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,with the outcome of the film.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.59,0:20:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But we thought in\Na couple of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.15,0:20:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that would all be forgotten\Nand move on with our life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.02,0:20:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I never dreamed that\N"Catch Me If You Can"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.77,0:20:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,would go on to earn more than\N$1 billion for Dreamworks
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.77,0:20:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and be shown over and over\Nliterally every week on HBO
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.07,0:20:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and TV and then become a\NBroadway musical and a TV show.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.39,0:20:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So consequently, every Monday\Nmorning when I come to work,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.20,0:20:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I have e-mails that come\Nfrom all over the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.38,0:20:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone who's seeing the\Nmovie for the first time,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.96,0:20:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,watching the play at a community\Ntheater or a high school
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.63,0:20:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,somewhere, and they\Nfeel compelled to write.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.66,0:20:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, they come from\Npeople literally as young
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.09,0:21:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,as eight years old sending those\Ne-mails to people as old as 80.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.11,0:21:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people assume I'll\Nnever read those e-mails
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.45,0:21:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,or see those e-mails.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.47,0:21:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But they feel\Ncompelled to write,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.21,0:21:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and they want to\Nmake a statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.92,0:21:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Some say, you know,\Nyou were brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.00,0:21:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You were an absolute genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.19,0:21:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I was neither.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.48,0:21:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.65,0:21:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Had I been brilliant,\Nhad I been a genius,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.72,0:21:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know that\NI would have found
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.22,0:21:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it necessary to break the law\Nin order to just simply survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.06,0:21:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And while I know that\Npeople are fascinated
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.85,0:21:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,by what I did some 50\Nyears ago as a teenage boy,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.41,0:21:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I've always looked\Nupon what I did
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.83,0:21:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,as something that was\Nimmoral, illegal, unethical,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.95,0:21:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and a burden I\Nlive with literally
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.02,0:21:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,every single day of my life,\Nand will until my death.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.50,0:21:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many\Nwho write and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.87,0:21:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,well, you know, you\Nwere certainly gifted.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.12,0:21:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.03,0:21:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I was one of those\Nfew children that
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.91,0:21:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,got to grow up in the\Nworld with a daddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.45,0:21:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the world is\Nfull of fathers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.79,0:21:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are very few men\Nworthy of being called daddy
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.66,0:22:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,by their child.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.26,0:22:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a daddy loved his children\Nmore than he loved life itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.59,0:22:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Steven Spielberg told Barbara\NWalters the [INAUDIBLE] I've
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.01,0:22:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,researched Frank's youth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.53,0:22:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Now without having met\NFrank, I couldn't help
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.08,0:22:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but put his father in the\Nfilm through the likes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.18,0:22:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of Christopher Walken.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.74,0:22:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,My father was a man who had\Nfour children-- three boys
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.29,0:22:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and a daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.77,0:22:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Every night at bedtime,\Nhe'd walk into your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.53,0:22:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He was 6', 3".
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.39,0:22:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He would drop down on one\Nknee, kiss you on the cheek,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.88,0:22:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,pull the cover up.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.66,0:22:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And he'd put his lip\Nup on your earlobe.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.00,0:22:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And he'd whisper deep into\Nyour ear, "I love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.07,0:22:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I love you very much."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.75,0:22:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He never ever missed a night.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.76,0:22:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,As I grew older, I sometimes\Nfell asleep before he got home.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.85,0:22:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But I always woke\Nup the next morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.83,0:22:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,knew he had been at my bedside.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.14,0:22:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Years later, my older\Nbrother joined me in my room
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.54,0:22:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,temporarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.35,0:22:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He was in the Marine Corps.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.64,0:22:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He was 6', 4".
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.57,0:22:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He played semi-pro\Nfootball for Buffalo.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.18,0:22:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But my father would\Nwalk around to his bed,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.45,0:22:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,hug him, kiss him, whisper\Nin his ear he loved him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.94,0:23:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was 16 years\Nold, I was just a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.36,0:23:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,All 16-year-olds\Nare just children.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.66,0:23:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Much as we'd like them to be\Nadults, they're just children.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.77,0:23:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And like all children,\Nthey need their mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.86,0:23:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and they need their father.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.57,0:23:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All children need their\Nmother and their father.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.20,0:23:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All children are entitled to\Ntheir mother and their father.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.15,0:23:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And though it is not\Npopular to say so,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.49,0:23:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,divorce is a very\Ndevastating thing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.89,0:23:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,for a child to\Ndeal with and then
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.84,0:23:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,have to deal with the rest\Nof their natural life.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.90,0:23:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,For me, a complete\Nstranger, a judge,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.88,0:23:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,told me I had to choose\None parent over the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.76,0:23:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a choice a\N16-year-old boy could not make.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.91,0:23:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So I ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.41,0:23:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,How could I tell you\Nmy life was glamorous?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.48,0:23:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I cried myself to sleep\N'til I was 19 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.75,0:23:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I spent every birthday,\NChristmas, Mother's Day,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.21,0:23:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Father's Day in a\Nhotel room somewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.95,0:23:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world where people\Ndidn't speak my language.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.34,0:23:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The only people that\Nassociated with me
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.26,0:24:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,were people who believed\Nme to be their peer,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.59,0:24:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,10 years older than\NI actually was.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.27,0:24:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I never got to go to a senior\Nprom, high school football
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.18,0:24:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,game, share a relationship\Nwith someone my own age.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.36,0:24:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I always knew I'd get caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.18,0:24:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Only a fool would\Nthink otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.39,0:24:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The law sometimes sleeps,\Nbut the law never dies.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.74,0:24:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I was caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.79,0:24:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to some very bad places.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.13,0:24:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,My boys have grown up\Nasking their mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.94,0:24:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,why is it that dad gets up\Nin the middle of the night
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.15,0:24:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and goes down to the TV room?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.36,0:24:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you know he\Ndoesn't turn the TV on.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.42,0:24:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He just sits there all night.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.11,0:24:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because there are\Nthings you can't forget,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.47,0:24:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,things you're not\Nmeant to forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.36,0:24:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,While I was sitting in that\Npitch black cell in France,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.70,0:24:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,my father, 57, was climbing\Nthe subway stairs in New York
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.76,0:24:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,as he did every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.63,0:24:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He was in great physical shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.00,0:24:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He just happened to trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.89,0:24:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He reached his arm\Nto break his fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.75,0:24:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He slipped, hit his\Nhead on the railing,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.10,0:24:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,landed at the\Nbottom of the step.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.47,0:24:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He was dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.76,0:24:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know he was dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.10,0:24:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I was thinking\Nabout him, how much
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.52,0:25:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't wait to see him, hold\Nhim, hug him, kiss him, tell
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.06,0:25:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,him how sorry I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.57,0:25:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But I never got the\Nopportunity to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.61,0:25:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I was very fortunate\Nbecause I was
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.28,0:25:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,raised in a great country where\Neveryone gets a second chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.57,0:25:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I owe my country 800 times\Nmore than I can ever repay it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.86,0:25:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,over these past four decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.15,0:25:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why I am\Nat the FBI today
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.36,0:25:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,32 years after the federal\Ncourt order expired
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.59,0:25:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,requiring me to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.50,0:25:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I have turned down three pardons\Nfrom three sitting presidents
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.68,0:25:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of the United States\Nbecause I do not believe,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.77,0:25:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,nor will I ever believe,\Nthat a piece of paper
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.10,0:25:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,will excuse my actions,\Nthat only in the end,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.97,0:25:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,my actions will.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.11,0:25:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,40 plus years ago, on\Nan undercover assignment
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.66,0:25:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,in Houston, Texas,\NI met my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.51,0:25:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,When the assignment was\Nover, I broke protocol
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.39,0:25:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to tell her who I really was.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.41,0:25:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't have a dime to my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.50,0:25:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But I eventually\Nasked her to marry me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.69,0:26:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Against the wishes of\Nher parents, she did.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.79,0:26:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I could sit up here and\Ntell you that I was born again,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.44,0:26:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw the light, prison\Nrehabilitated me.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.22,0:26:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But the truth is\NGod gave me a wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.55,0:26:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,She gave me three\Nbeautiful children.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.65,0:26:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,She gave me a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.19,0:26:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And she changed my\Nlife, she and she alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.80,0:26:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything I have, everything\NI've achieved, who I am today
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.19,0:26:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is because of the\Nlove of a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.44,0:26:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And the respect three\Nboys have for their father
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.81,0:26:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,is something I would\Nnever ever jeopardize.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.90,0:26:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There comes a time in all of\Nour lifetime, we grow older.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.48,0:26:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And eventually, if\Nwe're fortunate enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.37,0:26:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,we have children.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.87,0:26:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And as every parent knows,\Nwhether your child's
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.91,0:26:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,three months old\Nor 38 years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.24,0:26:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,when you lay ahead\Non a pillow at night,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.07,0:26:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you're just about\Nto close your eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.02,0:26:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the last thing you think about,\Nthe last thing you worry about
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.44,0:26:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,are your children.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.04,0:26:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you still\Nhave your mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.17,0:26:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you still have your father,\Nyou give them a hug.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.25,0:26:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You give them a kiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.70,0:26:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You tell them you love\Nthem while you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.50,0:27:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And to those men in the\Naudience, both young and old,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.71,0:27:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I would remind you what it\Ntruly is to actually be a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.47,0:27:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It has absolutely nothing to\Ndo with money, achievements,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.50,0:27:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,skills, accomplishments,\Ndegrees, professions,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.74,0:27:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,positions.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.41,0:27:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,A real man loves his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.92,0:27:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,A real man is\Nfaithful to his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.55,0:27:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And real men, next to\NGod and his country,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.36,0:27:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,put his wife and his children\Nas the most important thing
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.70,0:27:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.11,0:27:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Steven Spielberg made\Na wonderful film.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.12,0:27:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But I've done nothing greater,\Nnothing more rewarding, nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.18,0:27:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,more worthwhile,\Nnothing that's actually
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.10,0:27:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,brought me more peace, more joy,\Nmore happiness, more content
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.16,0:27:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,in my life than simply being\Na good husband, a good father,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.93,0:27:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and what I strive to be\Nevery day of my life--
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.88,0:27:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,a great daddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.87,0:27:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless you, and thanks\Nfor coming this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.95,0:27:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.50,0:27:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,[APPLAUSE]
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.92,0:27:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.33,0:28:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a bunch of questions\Nboth from the audience as well
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.59,0:28:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,as some people that sent in.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.79,0:28:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll take some questions\NI'll be happy to answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.14,0:28:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,AUDIENCE: Do you have\Nany advice for Googlers
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.01,0:28:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,who are feeling imposter\Nsyndrome, the insecure feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.17,0:28:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that they're not nearly\Nas good at their job
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.98,0:28:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,as their colleagues\Nbelieve they are?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.93,0:28:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And how did you stay\Nconfident, or did you,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.51,0:28:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,when you knew where\Nyou were an imposter?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.01,0:28:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,FRANK ABAGNALE: You know,\Npeople always say to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.15,0:28:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, you were brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.17,0:28:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You were a genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.98,0:28:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I was an adolescent.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.72,0:28:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was why\NI was successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.00,0:28:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so young that I had\Nno fear of being caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.33,0:28:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so young that I didn't\Nthink about consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.87,0:28:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything I did was\Nnot premeditated.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.93,0:28:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything was done by\Nopportunity or by chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.57,0:28:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So if, in fact, I\Nwas standing out
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.12,0:28:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,in front of a bank in\NManhattan with a $500 check,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.91,0:28:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,there was never a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.33,0:28:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't say to myself, I'm\Ngoing in, cash this check.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.04,0:29:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If they say this, I'll do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.08,0:29:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If they do this, I'll do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.72,0:29:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I just went in and did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.62,0:29:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And I felt that there was\Nnothing I couldn't do.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.17,0:29:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I had tremendous\Nconfidence in myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.17,0:29:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But everything was for a reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.82,0:29:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So I saw that airline crew.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.57,0:29:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I never dreamed about\Ngetting on planes
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.51,0:29:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,or staying in hotels\Naround the world for free.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.61,0:29:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All I saw was a uniform\Nand said to myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.68,0:29:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,if I had that uniform on,\Nand I walked in a bank,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.28,0:29:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be a lot easier to\Ncash a check than me walking in
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.40,0:29:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,as just some young kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.85,0:29:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So the whole thing was to\Nget a uniform and do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.97,0:29:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But then I quickly\Nrealized the power
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.61,0:29:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,of that uniform, how it\Nturned from night to day.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.22,0:29:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No one ever said\Nno when I walked
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.90,0:29:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in to cash a check, even though\Nthere was no bank account there
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.88,0:29:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,or anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.59,0:29:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,All they saw was the uniform.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.12,0:29:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.80,0:29:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And I realized very early on\Nthe power of that uniform.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.01,0:29:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I realized I'd\Ngone to the TWA ticket
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.07,0:29:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,counter just like he\Nshowed in the movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.23,0:29:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to purchase\Nan airline ticket.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.51,0:29:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And the ticket agent said to\Nme, "Are you riding for free,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.15,0:29:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,or are you buying the ticket?"
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.77,0:29:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said, riding for free?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.29,0:30:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,"Yeah, you on the jumpseat?"
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.89,0:30:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And I learned\Nabout the jumpseat.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.55,0:30:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So then I flew around\Nthe world for free.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.34,0:30:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything I did,\NI did by chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.19,0:30:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I moved into an apartment\Ncomplex in Atlanta.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.57,0:30:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I said I was a doctor\Nbecause I didn't want
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.42,0:30:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to write down airline pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.86,0:30:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They were looking for me\Nwith that airline pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.53,0:30:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So I said I was a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.24,0:30:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I said pediatrician because\Nit was a singles complex,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.42,0:30:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and there were only single\Npeople living there.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.67,0:30:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I met a\Ndoctor who lived there.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.34,0:30:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he took me\Nup to the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.96,0:30:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And I met people.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.82,0:30:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So I ended up at the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.61,0:30:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I dated a flight attendant\Nwhose father was the attorney
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.10,0:30:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,general in Louisiana.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.66,0:30:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I told her that I had\Ngone to law school,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.61,0:30:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,but I never practiced law.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.69,0:30:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, I wanted to be a pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.04,0:30:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And I got furloughed\Nfrom the airline.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.14,0:30:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So she introduced me to her dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.35,0:30:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And I went to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.14,0:30:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything was all these\Nopportunities, but always
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.63,0:30:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the confidence that\NI could pull it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.02,0:30:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And that became just from age.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.01,0:30:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you believe that you're\Ngood at what you do, and you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.61,0:30:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,strive to be good\Nat what you do,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.44,0:30:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't need to worry about\Nwhat other people think.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.69,0:30:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to be\Nable to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.22,0:30:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have your\Nown confidence
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.72,0:31:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can do whatever it\Nis you're required to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.78,0:31:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And other people will see\Nthat confidence in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.33,0:31:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you start\Ndoubting yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.82,0:31:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,other people will see that\Nyou are doubting yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.06,0:31:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And that becomes a weakness\Nin your personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.45,0:31:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So you always want you to\Nbe confident in everything
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.62,0:31:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you do that you can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.72,0:31:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You can get it done.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.55,0:31:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll find a way\Nto get it done.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.51,0:31:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,AUDIENCE: Obviously, technology\Nhas evolved quite a bit
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.80,0:31:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,since you were going\Naround, things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.29,0:31:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Would somebody be able\Nto accomplish something
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.36,0:31:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,similar today, even with all\Nof the technical advances?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.53,0:31:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,FRANK ABAGNALE: Yeah, you\Nknow, I get asked that a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.82,0:31:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, it's, sorry to say,\Nbut 4,000 times easier today
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.81,0:31:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,than when I did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.91,0:31:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Technology breeds crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.88,0:31:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It always has, and\Nit always will.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.11,0:31:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And there will always be people\Nwilling to use technology
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.23,0:31:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in a self-serving way.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.87,0:31:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So you know, I always\Nuse the example
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.67,0:31:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that when I used\Nto forge checks,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.65,0:31:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I needed a Heidelberg\Nprinting press.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.48,0:31:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It took me about 12 months\Nto learn that press.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.36,0:31:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That was $1 million\Nprinting press.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.11,0:32:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It was 90 feet\Nlong, 18 feet high.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.83,0:32:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It required three journeymen\Noperators to operate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.50,0:32:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So I built scaffoldings on\Neither sides of the press
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.50,0:32:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,so I could eliminate\Nthe other two positions.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.48,0:32:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And because I was\Na teenager, I was
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.34,0:32:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,able to run the\Nlength of that press.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.44,0:32:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But there were\Ncolor separations.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.09,0:32:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,There were negatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.96,0:32:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,There were chemicals\Nyou had to work with.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.71,0:32:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There were plates\Nyou had to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.13,0:32:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,There was typesetting involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.33,0:32:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, one just opens\Na laptop and decides
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.05,0:32:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to forge a counterfeited check.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.84,0:32:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,They first bring up\Na diagram of a check
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.22,0:32:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,with a little security\Nbackground in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.68,0:32:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And then they go and\Nlook on whose check
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.46,0:32:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,they're going to forge.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.42,0:32:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I'm going to forge,\Nfor example, Intuit's check,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.20,0:32:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I go to their company's\Nwebsite, capture their logo,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.41,0:32:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and put it up on the corner\Nof the left top of the check.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.35,0:32:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I put in their\Ncorporate address.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.28,0:32:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I might put some stuff in the\Nbackground, step and repeat
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.91,0:32:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,patterns or whatever\Nit is I'm designing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.13,0:32:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And in 15 minutes, I have a\Nfour color, beautiful check,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.55,0:32:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,prettier than the real check\Nthey use, up on my website.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.33,0:32:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now in the old days,\Nyou would've said to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.77,0:33:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, this check\Nyou printed for Pan Am?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.61,0:33:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to admit,\Nit's pretty awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.67,0:33:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's amazing, four\Ncolor, it looks terrific.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.28,0:33:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But let me ask you this.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.64,0:33:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know\Nwhere Pan Am banks?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.28,0:33:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no idea where they bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.60,0:33:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm just making\Nup a bank's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.61,0:33:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Chase Manhattan Bank, Morgan\NChase Plaza, New York,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.86,0:33:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.67,0:33:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know the\Naccount number is?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.47,0:33:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,No idea, I'm just making\Nup a bunch of numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.65,0:33:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know who the\Nauthorized signer is?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.65,0:33:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.19,0:33:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just signing\Nsomebody as Joe Black,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.27,0:33:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever name on a check.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.01,0:33:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But we live in a way-too-much\Ninformation world today.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.87,0:33:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So once I forge Intuit's\Ncheck, every forger
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.98,0:33:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,calls their victim twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.12,0:33:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Because every\Nforger will tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.54,0:33:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,a victim will tell me\Neverything I need to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.30,0:33:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So when he calls, he\Nwould have simply said,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.24,0:33:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,"Like to speak to someone\Nin accounts receivables."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.44,0:33:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,"Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.94,0:33:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,One moment."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.56,0:33:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,"Accounts receivables,\Ncan I help you?"
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.99,0:33:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,"Yeah, I was getting ready to\Npay an invoice you sent us.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.37,0:33:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But we prefer to\Nwire you the funds.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.22,0:33:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Just needed wiring\Ninstructions."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.79,0:33:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,"Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.32,0:33:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We bank with Bank of America.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.64,0:33:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Our account number is 176853."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.76,0:34:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They tell you\Nright on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.15,0:34:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You can call any company\Nand just tell them
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.94,0:34:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to wire them money.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.87,0:34:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They're going to tell\Nyou where they bank,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.01,0:34:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,on what street, their\Naccount number--
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.65,0:34:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,what you need on the check.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.77,0:34:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So I captured the bank's\Nlogo, I put it on the check.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.06,0:34:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I put the MICR line\Ndown on the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.09,0:34:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And I hang up and call back.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.45,0:34:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,"Intuit Corporation,\Ncan I help you?"
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.99,0:34:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'd like to\Nspeak to someone
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.41,0:34:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,in your corporate\Ncommunications.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.42,0:34:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,"Sure, one moment."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.37,0:34:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,"Corporate communications,\Ncan I help you?"
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.16,0:34:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I wondered if you'd\Nbe so kind as to mail me
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.31,0:34:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,a copy of your annual report.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.07,0:34:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,"Sure, I'll send\Nyou one out today.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.67,0:34:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,On page three is a\Nsignature of the chairman
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.56,0:34:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of the board, the CEO,\Nthe CFO, the treasurer.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.23,0:34:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,White glossy paper, black ink.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.85,0:34:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Camera ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.48,0:34:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, scan it, digitize\Nit, put it on the check.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.56,0:34:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The technology has made\Nit much, much easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.71,0:34:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we talk about IDs,\Nmaking an airline ID today
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.44,0:34:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,would be very simple with\Nthe technology that's
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.40,0:34:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,available today.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.54,0:34:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So all of those things\Nare a lot easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.20,0:34:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,As I used to say, it would\Nbe a little more difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.54,0:34:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,for me to get on an aircraft\Ntoday posing as a pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.64,0:34:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you ever\Ngo to the airport
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.01,0:34:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and watch the crews go\Nthrough the airport,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.81,0:35:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,they just simply hold\Nup a card, and they
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.03,0:35:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,go through the airport.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.41,0:35:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone could make that card with\Ntoday's software and technology
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.16,0:35:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that's available to anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.42,0:35:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So yeah, technology has\Ncertainly made it a lot easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.33,0:35:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why we are\Nconstantly making technology
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.69,0:35:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to counter the use of\Ntechnology by criminals
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.64,0:35:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and to make it more\Ndifficult for them
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.22,0:35:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to convert that technology\Ninto a negative idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.94,0:35:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,AUDIENCE: In your\Ncandid opinion,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.38,0:35:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,did Leonardo DiCaprio and\NTom Hanks do justice to your
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.86,0:35:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and Joseph Shea's respective\Nroles in the movie?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.48,0:35:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,FRANK ABAGNALE: Yeah, you know,\NI'm not a big movie person.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.94,0:35:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So I watch very\Nlittle television.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.34,0:35:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This is most of\Nmy life, not just
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.83,0:35:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,something I took\Nup even as a kid,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.50,0:35:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't watch a\Nlot of television.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.96,0:35:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't watch a lot\Nof television now,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.54,0:35:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and I certainly very\Nrarely go to movies.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.43,0:35:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So when it was\Nannounced that Leo
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.61,0:35:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,was the person picked\Nto play the part,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.32,0:35:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I really knew nothing about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.33,0:35:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,My sons weren't too\Nhappy that it was Leo.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.73,0:35:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But I didn't know\Nanything about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.01,0:35:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So I went to the movies and\Nsaw "Street Gangs of New York."
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.31,0:36:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said to myself\Nsitting there, how would
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.74,0:36:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,this person portray a\Nperson 16 years old?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.46,0:36:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He had a beard.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.63,0:36:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time he filmed that\Nmovie, he was about 27,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.28,0:36:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,28 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.34,0:36:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, no one's going\Nto believe this guy is 16.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.71,0:36:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But because I never\Nsaw the script,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.42,0:36:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know if maybe Spielberg\Nwas making the character
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.88,0:36:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot older and not a teenager.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.16,0:36:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,When the movie came out,\Nit was quite amazing
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.26,0:36:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that Leo starts out in the\Nfilm at 14, then he's 16,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.36,0:36:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,then he's 18, then he's 21.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.66,0:36:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He is an amazing\Ncharacter actor.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.70,0:36:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And he took the role,\Nand he did an amazing job
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.17,0:36:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,of playing the role.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.54,0:36:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Tom Hanks' character was\Nactually named Joe Shea,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.63,0:36:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,S-H-E-A. He was an\NIrishman from Boston.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.51,0:36:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Joe Shea was my\Nsupervisor at the FBI
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.61,0:36:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,after I came out of prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.81,0:36:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I answered directly to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.28,0:36:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He and I were friends for\N30 years until his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.64,0:36:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I've written five\Nbooks on crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.44,0:36:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The last book I wrote,\N"Stealing Your Life,"
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.30,0:36:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I dedicated that book to him\Nand our 30-year relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.11,0:36:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But he was an\NIrishman from Boston,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.79,0:36:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,which Tom Hanks-- he didn't\Nwant his real name used.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.71,0:37:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So Tom Hanks used the name\Nof an old football player
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.79,0:37:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and took that name\NCarl Hanratty.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.46,0:37:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you were watching\Nthe screen, for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.74,0:37:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it was like watching him.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.06,0:37:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He looked like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.29,0:37:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He sounded like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.86,0:37:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He had his mannerisms.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.29,0:37:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They did an amazing\Njob, both of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.64,0:37:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in portraying the\Nparts of real people
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.55,0:37:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that were still\Nliving at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.70,0:37:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,AUDIENCE: So first\Nof all, as a father,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.32,0:37:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,your statement was\Njust got me tearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.50,0:37:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm not gonna ask\Nyou anything about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.37,0:37:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna ask totally\Npractical with the Equifax
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.83,0:37:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,hacks and the Anthem hacks\Nthat everyone in this room
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.05,0:37:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,has been probably affected\Nby one or the other,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.02,0:37:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is there anything we can do as\Ncitizens to protect ourselves?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.10,0:37:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Or is it a lost cause?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.66,0:37:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,FRANK ABAGNALE: No, I'll\Ntell you what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.69,0:37:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But let me explain this to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.12,0:37:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That is where-- when I went\Nto the FBI 41 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.27,0:37:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I worked undercover for\Na long period of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.06,0:37:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I went into\Nthe field and dealt
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.80,0:37:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,with counterfeits and forgeries,\Nembezzlement, financial crimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.50,0:37:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In the last 20 years, I've dealt\Nwith only cyber-related crimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.72,0:38:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So I spend most of my\Ntime with breeches.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.88,0:38:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I have worked every breech\Nback to TJ Maxx 15 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.78,0:38:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is what I've learned.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.43,0:38:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, every\Nsingle breach--
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.30,0:38:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,every breach occurs because\Nsomebody in that company
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.29,0:38:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,did something they\Nweren't supposed to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.10,0:38:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,or somebody in\Nthat company failed
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.93,0:38:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to do something they\Nwere supposed to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.05,0:38:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Hackers do not cause breaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.47,0:38:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,People do.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.30,0:38:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And every breach\Ncomes down to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.44,0:38:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the case of\NEquifax, they didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.29,0:38:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,update their infrastructure.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.67,0:38:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That didn't fix the patches\Nthey should've put in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.47,0:38:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,There were very negligent\Nin what they were doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.17,0:38:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So the hacker waited\Nfor the door to open.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.50,0:38:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you interview a hacker,\Nthe hacker will say to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.96,0:38:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,look, I can't get\Ninto Chase Bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.59,0:38:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is they spend about\Na half a billion dollars a year
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.13,0:38:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,on technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.12,0:38:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Every 12 months, they spend\Na half a billion dollars
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.02,0:38:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,of their profit on putting\Ntechnology and software
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.94,0:38:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in their bank to keep me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.34,0:39:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,However, they employ\N200,000 people worldwide.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.87,0:39:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,All I have to do is wait\Nfor one of those people
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.26,0:39:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to do something they\Nweren't supposed to do
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.12,0:39:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,or failed to do what\Nthey were supposed to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.82,0:39:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And that'll open the\Ndoor for me to get in.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.96,0:39:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,When you steal\Ncredit card numbers
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.06,0:39:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,like Home Depot,\NTarget, TJ Maxx, that's
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.63,0:39:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,stealing credit cards and\Ndebit card information,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.13,0:39:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that has a very short,\Nshort shelf life.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.47,0:39:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have to get rid\Nof it very, very quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.18,0:39:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I steal your name,\Nyour social security
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.54,0:39:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,number, and your date of birth,\Nyou can't change your name.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.33,0:39:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't change your\Nsocial security number.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.39,0:39:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't change\Nyour date of birth.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.58,0:39:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So those people warehouse that\Ndata for two to three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.48,0:39:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So we won't even see that\Nsurface for at least a couple
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.71,0:39:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of years before some of\Nthat will start to surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.23,0:39:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the data that was stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.12,0:39:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever number\Nthey start with--
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.59,0:39:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was 143 million,\Nthen it became 146 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.25,0:39:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a million\Ndrivers licenses, now
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.53,0:39:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,it's 10.6 million\Ndrivers licenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.10,0:40:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Are all breaches start\Nwith very low numbers
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.60,0:40:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,before they let you know\Nthe actual true numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.73,0:40:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's probably about 240\Nmillion pieces of information
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.69,0:40:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that were stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.13,0:40:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But I remind people all\Nthe time that they're
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.83,0:40:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,going to warehouse that data.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.42,0:40:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So buying one-year credit\Nmonitoring services
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.66,0:40:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is absolutely worthless\Nbecause nothing's
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.92,0:40:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,going to happen in a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.48,0:40:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you really\Nanalyze Equifax,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.36,0:40:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,they were very unethical\Nin what they did.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.17,0:40:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They thought to\Nthemselves-- first of all,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.92,0:40:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,they sold a bunch\Nof stock knowing
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.55,0:40:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that it was going to come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.80,0:40:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That was worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.86,0:40:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But then they sat there\Nand said, how do we
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.65,0:40:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,make a profit from this?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.91,0:40:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It was our mistake, but\Nhow do we turn this around
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.99,0:40:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,into a profit?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.42,0:40:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So they sat there\Nand said, what we'll
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.01,0:40:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,do is we'll offer millions\Nand millions of people
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.86,0:40:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,one-year credit monitoring\Nservice for free.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.07,0:40:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll sign up.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.18,0:40:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And in a year from\Nnow, we'll simply
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.86,0:40:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,say that data hasn't\Nreally surfaced yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.35,0:40:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to be\Nenrolled automatically
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.00,0:40:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,into our program,\Nwhich is $20 a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.86,0:40:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So they're going to make\Nmillions and millions
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.78,0:41:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of dollars with automatic\Nenrollment into their program.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.09,0:41:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've been a\Nsubject of that breach,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.57,0:41:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,there's only two things you\Ncan do, and two things only.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.63,0:41:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,One, you can freeze your credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.24,0:41:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Each state varies about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.89,0:41:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So some states, freezing\Nyour credit is free.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.50,0:41:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Other states, there's a fee\Nassociated with it, typically
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.77,0:41:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,$10 to freeze it,\N$18 to unfreeze,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.10,0:41:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,$10 to freeze it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.78,0:41:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So for the last two years,\NI've testified before Congress.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.68,0:41:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And you go to my\Nwebsite at abagnale.com.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.99,0:41:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll see me testifying\Nbefore Congress telling them
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.30,0:41:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that they need to put a federal\Nlaw across the 50 states that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.20,0:41:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,allow anyone to freeze\Ntheir credit at any time
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.00,0:41:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and unfreeze it at any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.88,0:41:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,There should be no\Nreason that there
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.41,0:41:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,should be a fee associated\Nwith it because then
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.75,0:41:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that becomes a deterrent\Nto people actually
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.84,0:41:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,freezing their credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.31,0:41:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can freeze your credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.56,0:41:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one thing you can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.73,0:41:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you unfreeze\Nit if you need it,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.37,0:41:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,if it's not too\Nmuch of a hassle.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.27,0:41:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the only other thing\Nis to monitor your credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.51,0:42:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So I've used a credit\Nmonitoring service since 1992.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.75,0:42:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So for about 25 years,\NI've been using a service.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.11,0:42:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I think they charge\Nme like $12 a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.47,0:42:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason I like it, I\Ncan monitor my own credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.86,0:42:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need them.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.82,0:42:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,All they've given\Nme for that $12
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.83,0:42:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is the ability to go on my\Nkeyboard in a few strokes
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.89,0:42:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and bring up my credit reports\Ninstantly on my screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.10,0:42:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And up on my screen\Ncomes all three reports--
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.10,0:42:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Equifax, Experian, TransUnion.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.56,0:42:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,At the top is my score for\Nthe moment of that day,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.35,0:42:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,what my credit score is\Nat those three agencies.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.23,0:42:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I can scroll down\Nand look at my credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.74,0:42:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can say to\Nmyself, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.16,0:42:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I paid this car off\Nlike four months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.08,0:42:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They still show that I\Nowe money to this bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.50,0:42:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll correct that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.13,0:42:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can go all the way\Ndown and see every inquiry
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.83,0:42:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,made on my credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.00,0:42:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what we call\Nhard and soft inquiries.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.61,0:42:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's your\Nemployer checking
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.44,0:42:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,your credit, the IRS\Nchecking your credit,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.51,0:42:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,your insurance company\Nchecking your credit,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.34,0:42:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,or a credit card\Nyou applied for,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.53,0:42:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're checking\Nyour credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.12,0:42:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So I really don't need them.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.74,0:43:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But for a fee, they're also\Nmonitoring my credit as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.93,0:43:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So they're checking\Nmy credit, and they're
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.68,0:43:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,letting me know in real\Ntime if someone attempts
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.81,0:43:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to use my social security\Nnumber to get a job,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.42,0:43:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,open a bank account, or\Nwhatever the case may be.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.10,0:43:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So to me, it's worth using that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.39,0:43:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, one other tip I'll give\Nyou is I don't own a debit card.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.36,0:43:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never owned one.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.56,0:43:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never allowed my\Nthree sons to possess one.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.16,0:43:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly and truly the\Nworst financial tool
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.88,0:43:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,ever given to the\NAmerican consumer.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.10,0:43:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So a long time ago, I asked\Nmyself a simple question.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.01,0:43:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,How would I remove 99.9% of my\Npersonal liability like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.17,0:43:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I really don't want to\Nworry about all these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.08,0:43:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So I use the safest\Nform of payment
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.87,0:43:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that exists on the\Nface of the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.79,0:43:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is a credit card.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.52,0:43:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Credit card-- Visa,\NMasterCard, American Express,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.76,0:43:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Discover card.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.02,0:43:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Not debit-credit,\Nbut credit card.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.74,0:44:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day of my life,\NI spend their money.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.20,0:44:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't spend my money.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.16,0:44:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,My money sits in a\Nmoney market account.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.83,0:44:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It earns interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.52,0:44:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, nobody knows\Nwhere it is because it's not
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.65,0:44:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,exposed to anybody to find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.27,0:44:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just sitting there.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.56,0:44:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I go to the dry cleaner,\NI give them my card.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.57,0:44:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I pick up the groceries,\NI give them my card.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.58,0:44:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I put fuel in my boat on\Nthe weekend, I use my card.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.16,0:44:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I pay the marina to keep my\Nboat in the water all year long,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.98,0:44:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,they put the rent\Non my credit card.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.35,0:44:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I travel all over the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.18,0:44:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,While I wait to get reimbursed,\NI use my credit card.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.70,0:44:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,If I need euros, I go to the ATM\Nmachine, I use my credit card.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.61,0:44:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to use my debit\Ncard to get euros overseas
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.66,0:44:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,or a pounds in Great Britain.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.18,0:44:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And every day, I use my card.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.86,0:44:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And then if I pay the bill\Nin full or part of the bill,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.74,0:44:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,my credit score goes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.30,0:44:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm building credit while\NI'm using that credit card.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.72,0:44:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And if tomorrow-- and\NI'll do everything
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.61,0:44:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to protect my information--\Nbut if tomorrow someone gets
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.91,0:44:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,my card number and charges\N$1 million on my credit card,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.09,0:44:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,by federal law, my\Nliability is zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.54,0:45:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no liability.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.17,0:45:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So yes, I love to shop online.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.23,0:45:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't use a special card.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.58,0:45:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I just use my credit card.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.11,0:45:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If they don't deliver\Nthe merchandise,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.12,0:45:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,if they deliver it\Nand it's broken,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.13,0:45:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,if the host site I went to\Nwas fictitious to begin with,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.10,0:45:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I have zero liability.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.87,0:45:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,When you use your debit card,\Nevery time you reach for it,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.29,0:45:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you're exposing the\Nmoney in your account.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.18,0:45:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The only person who's\Ngoing to get robbed is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.64,0:45:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,When you use your\Ndebit card, you
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.05,0:45:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,could use it for the next\N50 years 20 times a day,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.79,0:45:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you will not raise your\Ncredit score by that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.51,0:45:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, when you\Nuse your debit card,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.81,0:45:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you are liable up\Nto a certain amount.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.55,0:45:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And it takes a while in order\Nto get that debit card fixed.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.66,0:45:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we do post\Ninvestigations at breaches,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.77,0:45:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and we say to someone on\Nyour incident, what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.28,0:45:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I was in Target.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.20,0:45:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But I used a Visa card.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.67,0:45:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So I don't know, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.53,0:45:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They canceled my\Ncard the next day.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.94,0:45:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Two days later, FedEx\Nsent me a new card.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.21,0:45:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was the last\NI heard about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.83,0:45:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.95,0:45:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And I used a debit card there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.33,0:45:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They took $3,000 out\Nof my checking account.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.08,0:46:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It took me two months\Nto get my money back
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.12,0:46:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,while they said they\Nwere investigating.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.89,0:46:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to pay my rent, had\Nkids' tuition, everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.77,0:46:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't pay it because\Nthey had my money.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.38,0:46:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So I do it for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.23,0:46:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So I had three sons that\Nwent off to college.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.11,0:46:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said to them, I'm not\Ngiving you a debit card.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.78,0:46:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I've actually applied for\Na credit card in your name.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.42,0:46:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's your card.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.26,0:46:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, you're 18.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.13,0:46:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You have no credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.15,0:46:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So I guarantee the card.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.01,0:46:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So as a guarantee-er of the\Ncard, three things take place.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.13,0:46:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,One, the bill comes to me, and\NI'm responsible for the bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.37,0:46:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you spend a lot\Nof time in the bar,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.08,0:46:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.37,0:46:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Two, I set the\Nlimit on the card.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.95,0:46:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So whatever I want you to\Nspend each month while you're
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.29,0:46:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,at school, I'll set that limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.39,0:46:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Third, every month that I pay\Nthe bill goes on your credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.06,0:46:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So by the time you\Nget out of college,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.73,0:46:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you should be looking at a\Ncredit score of about 800.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.34,0:46:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to buy a car,\Nbuy a house, buy a condo?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.80,0:46:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not going to\Nneed me to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.42,0:46:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,All three of my sons came\Nout of college with scores
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.87,0:46:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,up around 800.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.27,0:46:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the best things\Nyou can do for your kids
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.23,0:47:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is to teach them to learn\Nto use credit early on
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.10,0:47:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and build credit in their name.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.11,0:47:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Credit is a very\Nimportant thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.69,0:47:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,30 years ago, it only meant\Nwhether you got the car,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.86,0:47:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you got the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.55,0:47:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, everything is\Nbased on your credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.30,0:47:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If a company hires you, they're\Ngoing to check your credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.77,0:47:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If you buy auto\Ninsurance, they're
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.19,0:47:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,going to check your credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.09,0:47:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If you buy life\Ninsurance, they're
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.06,0:47:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,going to check your credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.46,0:47:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is based\Non your credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.11,0:47:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So you want to make sure that\Nyou maintain good credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.34,0:47:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's one of the best things\Nyou can do with your kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.45,0:47:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Question?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.41,0:47:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,AUDIENCE: I wanted\Nto ask you more
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.83,0:47:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,about the FBI specifically,\Nand kind of hiring
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.89,0:47:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and how you got in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.93,0:47:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It is such an interesting story.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.40,0:47:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, when I was\Nyounger I was really
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.11,0:47:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,interested in\Nworking for the FBI,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.21,0:47:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,worked in fraud and security.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.06,0:47:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If my boss is watching, I'm\Nvery happy where I am right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.43,0:47:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But I couldn't believe how\Ndifficult it was to try and get
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.13,0:47:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,into public service.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.06,0:47:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, you know, there's--
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.62,0:47:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I was willing to take a pay cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.15,0:47:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I was willing to move anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.44,0:47:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I was willing to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.22,0:47:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.20,0:47:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I was in touch\Nwith people at the FBI.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.12,0:47:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And they were super\Nnice and very helpful.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.13,0:48:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But I just couldn't believe\Nthe background checks,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.40,0:48:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's no available jobs,\Nand you have to keep e-mailing,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.03,0:48:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and oh, you don't\Nhave a law degree?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.98,0:48:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's not going to matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.27,0:48:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And you know, again, I\Nended up in a great spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.53,0:48:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.19,0:48:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But when people asked me about\Npublic service and working
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.24,0:48:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,for these organizations, I\Nreally don't have an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.91,0:48:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,FRANK ABAGNALE: Yeah, the\NFBI is extremely tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.95,0:48:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We have about 13,000 agents\Nand about 25,000 support people
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.11,0:48:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,who support the agents, analysts\Nand things of that nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.41,0:48:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Currently, we take one in\Nevery 10,000 applicants
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.60,0:48:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to be an agent.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.80,0:48:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So it is extremely\Ndifficult to get in the FBI.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.44,0:48:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So just to share\Nthe story with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.99,0:48:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,my oldest boy, when\Nhe was about 14,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.84,0:48:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to take my kids\Nto the FBI Academy, which
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.96,0:48:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is on a marine military\Nbase in Quantico, Virginia
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.63,0:48:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because they like to\Nshoot guns on the range,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.52,0:48:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and I would take them up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.81,0:48:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was teaching\Nclass, they would
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.46,0:48:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,be out there with the instructor\Nshooting on the range.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.85,0:48:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remember\Ndistinctly coming back
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.79,0:49:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,off the base, which takes\Nyou about 20 minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.74,0:49:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to get from the Academy\Noff to the base.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.08,0:49:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we were riding through\Nthe base, he said to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.41,0:49:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, dad, this\Nis what I want to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.55,0:49:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to become an FBI agent.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.42,0:49:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, well, that's great, son.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.75,0:49:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But keep that in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.70,0:49:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And so he graduated\Nfrom high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.27,0:49:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He said to me, I really\Nwant to become a FBI agent.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.97,0:49:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, that's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.84,0:49:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you gotta go to college.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.28,0:49:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So he went to school at\NUniversity of Kansas,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.32,0:49:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,got his undergraduate.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.40,0:49:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I always thought\Nhe'd change his mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.79,0:49:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife always had\Na Christmas party
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.92,0:49:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,for all the agents in Tulsa.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.35,0:49:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We had about 200 FBI\Nagents in the state.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.09,0:49:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And every Christmas,\Nthey would be at our home
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.40,0:49:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,with their family.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.60,0:49:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And he would go\Ntalk to all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.49,0:49:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Special\NAgent in charge who's
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.38,0:49:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in charge of the entire state,\Nhe would say to him, yeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.44,0:49:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,my son tried to get in.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.97,0:49:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But they turned him down.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.53,0:49:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And he explained to\Nhim that senator's sons
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.72,0:49:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,have been turned down.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.64,0:49:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Former presidents' sons\Nhave been turned down.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.13,0:49:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It has nothing to do with\Nanything other than you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.04,0:49:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And I kept emphasizing\Nthat to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.41,0:50:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But I kept thinking\Nhe'd change his mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.12,0:50:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So when he graduated from\Nundergraduate school,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.08,0:50:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, son, I would recommend\Nyou go to law school.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.82,0:50:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,"I have no desire\Nto be a lawyer."
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.24,0:50:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.11,0:50:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you really want\Nto pursue the FBI,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.72,0:50:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that would put you\Nup a little higher
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.76,0:50:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and your chances of getting in.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.33,0:50:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He went to Loyola School of Law.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.76,0:50:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He graduated from law school.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.17,0:50:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bureau requires\Nyou pass the bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.04,0:50:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So he took the bar in\NIllinois, passed the bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.37,0:50:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he went through\Nthe year-long process
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.29,0:50:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of the process it takes\Nto apply to the Bureau.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.74,0:50:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And I got very worried\Nbecause I'd say to my wife
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.56,0:50:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that, you know, I'm a little\Nconcerned because first of all,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.45,0:50:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if\Nsomeone in management
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.09,0:50:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,would like the fact that\Nmy son is an FBI agent.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.51,0:50:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Or maybe someone in\Nmanagement would look at it
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.67,0:50:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and say, his dad has\Ndone so much for them,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.89,0:50:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,we need to look at his son.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.32,0:50:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It had absolutely\Nnothing to do with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.57,0:50:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It was all about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.79,0:50:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And I always tell him every day\Nhe's living his life's dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.30,0:50:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So he got in.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.28,0:50:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But it is very, very tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.33,0:50:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So when the Bureau came to me--\Nand they just a few years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.80,0:51:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,celebrated their\N100th anniversary.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.45,0:51:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They did a big\Ncoffee table book,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.01,0:51:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and they talk about me in there\Nas being the only person they
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.16,0:51:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,ever did that with.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.81,0:51:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole thing to\Nthe Bureau back then,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.48,0:51:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the director was\NClarence Kelley,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.17,0:51:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,who was the Director of\Nthe Bureau at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.59,0:51:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted the ability because\Nhe could say to me, OK,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.82,0:51:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you are a lieutenant\Nin the Army.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.31,0:51:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You have been in the\NArmy this many years.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.86,0:51:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Your expertise is this missile.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.38,0:51:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I need you to learn all\Nof this in two weeks,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.75,0:51:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm sending\Nyou to this base.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.87,0:51:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And I want you to find\Nout what's going on
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.62,0:51:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,in this particular area.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.57,0:51:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew that no matter\Nwhat assignment he
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.49,0:51:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,gave me under cover,\NI could go do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.41,0:51:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it was a scientist\Nat a lab in New Mexico,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.11,0:51:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it was a\Ndoctor in a hospital,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.33,0:51:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,he knew that I could\Nget away with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.95,0:51:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,make people believe that I was\Nthat person without any doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.88,0:51:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's how they used me.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.18,0:51:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that was\Ntheir initial thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.52,0:51:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, of course, when\Nmy time was up-- and again,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.19,0:51:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,keep in mind that when\NI got that offer, to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.23,0:51:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it was just an opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.64,0:52:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I looked at it, well,\Nopportunity to get out of jail.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.14,0:52:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I am not going to\Nsit here and tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.14,0:52:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a changed person, that\NI was a different person
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.24,0:52:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,than when I went into prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.56,0:52:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I just saw that\Nas an opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.93,0:52:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to get out of prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.83,0:52:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was going to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.48,0:52:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But then you get involved with\Nthe men and women of the FBI
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.78,0:52:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,who obviously are probably the\Nmost ethical people you'll ever
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.75,0:52:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,meet in your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.87,0:52:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,They have tremendous\Ncharacter, love of country,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.87,0:52:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,love of family.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.16,0:52:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That kind of wears off on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.09,0:52:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And I started to realize\Nthat I met my wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.90,0:52:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was becoming a husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.32,0:52:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I take care of my wife, I take\Ncare of children, fatherhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.73,0:52:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,All those things is what\Nreally changed my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.01,0:52:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't that I was\Nrehabilitated or--
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.35,0:52:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,those things changed my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.62,0:52:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So it started out more\Nas an opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.08,0:52:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So when my time was\Nover, and the court said
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.14,0:52:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,his court order\Nceases to be, he's
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.54,0:52:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,free to do whatever\Nhe wants to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.55,0:52:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I made the choice\Nto stay there only
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.56,0:52:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,because I thought that I could\Nbring a lot to the Bureau.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.79,0:52:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Bureau was very smart.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.78,0:52:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They realized very\Nearly on that I
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.48,0:52:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't be accepted very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.95,0:53:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And so there was a great\Nscene in the movie where
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.99,0:53:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Steven Spielberg obviously\Nknew that I was very, very
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.31,0:53:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,difficult for the agents.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.92,0:53:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep in mind now\Nthis is back when
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.34,0:53:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,there were no women agents,\Nno blacks, no Hispanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.13,0:53:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was a white\Nagent, and they either
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.17,0:53:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,graduated from Harvard, or\Nthey graduated from Yale.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.99,0:53:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And they all came from\Nvery good families.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.69,0:53:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was a totally different\Nenvironment 40 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.49,0:53:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So they all had\Nreally tunnel vision--
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.43,0:53:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,once a criminal,\Nalways a criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.23,0:53:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So they were not very,\Nvery happy with the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.63,0:53:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that I came there.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.07,0:53:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So he showed that\Nscene of me walking
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.96,0:53:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,in the office and the\Nway people looked at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.77,0:53:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That took years for me\Nto turn that around.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.66,0:53:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Took years for me to\Nbuild their credibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.34,0:53:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, in the\Nfirst part of my career,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.31,0:53:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I was out in the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.42,0:53:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I was undercover.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.53,0:53:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So they really weren't\Ndealing with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.54,0:53:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I finished\Nworking under cover,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.40,0:53:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the director then simply\Nsaid, you know what?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.28,0:53:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He needs to go to the\NAcademy and teach class
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.65,0:53:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,so that every agent who\Ncomes to the Academy,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.95,0:54:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,he will be their instructor\Nin one of their courses.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.22,0:54:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And they will all know him.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.57,0:54:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So I've taught at the Academy\Nnow for well over 35 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.93,0:54:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I taught my son when I\Nwent through the Academy.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.39,0:54:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Three generations of agents.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.11,0:54:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And that helped a great\Ndeal because they learned
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.17,0:54:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,who I was early\Non, knew who I was,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.26,0:54:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and that changed a lot of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.65,0:54:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But it took a lot of work to\Nturn that around and build
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.68,0:54:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that credibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.69,0:54:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,AUDIENCE: I'm curious\Nto know whether or not
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.52,0:54:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,you continued to fly even after\Nyou were released from jail
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.75,0:54:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and working at the Bureau\Nas the movie suggests,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.12,0:54:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,or if that was a bit of\NHollywood embellishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.12,0:54:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,FRANK ABAGNALE: Now, you\Nknow, when people ask me--
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.25,0:54:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and I saw the movie\Nin a movie theater.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.47,0:54:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I've only seen the movie twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.12,0:54:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I've seen that\Ntrailer 1,000 times,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.98,0:54:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but I've only seen\Nthe movie twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.02,0:54:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So when the media asked me\Nwhat I thought about the movie
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.90,0:54:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and what was right\Nand what was wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.78,0:54:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, you know,\Nwell, first of all,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.32,0:54:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I have two brothers\Nand a sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.91,0:54:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He portrayed me\Nas an only child.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.88,0:54:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In real life, my\Nmother never remarried.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.63,0:54:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a scene in\Nthe movie where she's
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.30,0:54:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,remarried as a little girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.83,0:54:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That didn't really happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.99,0:55:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In the real life, I never saw\Nmy father after I ran away.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.68,0:55:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In the movie, they keep\Nhaving him come back
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.60,0:55:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to Christopher Walken\Nin the film who
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.15,0:55:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,was nominated for\Nthe Academy Award
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.81,0:55:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,for that role as my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.78,0:55:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That didn't really happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.59,0:55:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I escaped off the aircraft,\Nbut I escaped off the aircraft
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.67,0:55:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,through the kitchen galley where\Nthey bring the food and stuff
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.25,0:55:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,onto the plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.00,0:55:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And there they had me\Nescape through the toilet.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.69,0:55:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And my wife kind of\Nlooked at me and said,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.44,0:55:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,you didn't go through\Nthe toilet, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.70,0:55:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, no, I didn't\Ngo through the toilet.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.46,0:55:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought he stayed\Nvery close to the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.09,0:55:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But pretty much all of that--
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.69,0:55:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,he was very concerned about\Nbeing accurate, first of all,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.82,0:55:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,because it was the first\Ntime he made a movie
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.06,0:55:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,about a real person living.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.13,0:55:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, the Bureau had an\Ninformation officer on the set
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.31,0:55:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,for all the shooting\Nof the entire film
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.16,0:55:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to make sure that what\Nhe said about the FBI
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.44,0:55:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and what comments they made\Nand all that was accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.21,0:55:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There was an agent from our\Ninformation office on the set.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.46,0:55:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, of course,\Nas he later said,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.53,0:56:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,"I really got most\Nof my information
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.21,0:56:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,from those three\Nretired agents."
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.34,0:56:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he said their notes were\Nso particular and so accurate
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.31,0:56:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,he said that "when I filmed\Nthe scene in the hotel room,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.13,0:56:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I had scripted it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.87,0:56:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we're sitting there, and\NI said, read me your notes."
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.35,0:56:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, "I entered the\Nroom with my gun pulled.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.57,0:56:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard someone in the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.52,0:56:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I ordered them to come\Nout of the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.80,0:56:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is what happened."
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.24,0:56:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He basically loved his notes\Nbetter than his script.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.19,0:56:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So he used his\Nnotes for the film.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.94,0:56:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought he did a good\Njob of staying very, very
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.78,0:56:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,accurate at the movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.12,0:56:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll just make a\Nfinal comment to you
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.06,0:56:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,having to deal with cyber now.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.70,0:56:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I like to write about\Ncrimes in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.85,0:56:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So I always used to\Nwrite to my class
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.97,0:56:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,about what will we investigate\Nfive years from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.40,0:56:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What will an agent be\Ndoing five years from now?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.57,0:56:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And unfortunately, there's good\Nnews, and there's bad news.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.23,0:56:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, the\Ngood news, we will
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.88,0:57:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,be doing away with passwords\Nin the next 24 months.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.64,0:57:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Passwords will leave the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.69,0:57:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There will be no more passwords.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.75,0:57:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a new technology\Ncalled Trusona.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.27,0:57:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's T-R-U-S-O-N-A.\NStands for true persona.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.34,0:57:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a company in\NScottsdale, Arizona
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.14,0:57:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that created a\Ntechnology for the CIA
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.99,0:57:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,which we have used now\Nfor the last few years.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.87,0:57:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That technology--\Nand I was an adviser
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.75,0:57:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,on that technology for the CIA.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.94,0:57:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm an advisor on bringing\Nit to the commercial world.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.63,0:57:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was the\Nability for an agent
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.40,0:57:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to send data back from the\Nfield, such as Afghanistan,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.54,0:57:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,on their iPhone, and that\NLangley would know 100% that
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.97,0:57:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is the agent on the\Nother end, to 100%
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.88,0:57:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,identify the person on the\Nother end of the device.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.72,0:57:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the level four security.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.73,0:57:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So they basically\Nsaid, what if we
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.83,0:57:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,brought this to\Nlevel two security,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.56,0:57:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and we did away with passwords?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.00,0:57:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So immediately,\Nwhen they announced
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.46,0:58:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that, Microsoft gave them\N$10 million and said, I'm in.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.21,0:58:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Develop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.82,0:58:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So Microsoft is\Ngoing to use that
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.19,0:58:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,on all their gaming,\Nall their access
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.75,0:58:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to their computers, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.43,0:58:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We now have the\Nability to identify
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.49,0:58:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,who the person is on the\Nother end of that device.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.65,0:58:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you go to their\Nwebsite at Trusona,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.01,0:58:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,they actually show\Nyou how it's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.58,0:58:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So they show you\Ndemo videos there
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.21,0:58:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that are three or\Nfour minutes long
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.67,0:58:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that show you how it's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.22,0:58:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.05,0:58:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Passwords are stagnant.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.35,0:58:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They should have been\Ngone long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.06,0:58:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's why we have most of the\Nproblems that we have today.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.91,0:58:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So it is very important that\Nwe get rid of passwords.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.15,0:58:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And just in case\Nyou didn't know,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.92,0:58:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,if we take a bank like\Na Bank of America,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.44,0:58:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,they spend about $6 million\Na month in their call center
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.46,0:58:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,resetting passwords.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.84,0:58:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Costs them $6 million a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.95,0:58:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So that would save that\Nbank $100 million a year
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.91,0:58:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to eliminate the\Nuse of passwords.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.07,0:58:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the good part of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.76,0:58:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think that will\Neventually do away
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.43,0:58:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,with social security numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.90,0:58:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll still have a\Nnumber assigned to you
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.06,0:58:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,for the government purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.48,0:58:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But when I go by a car,\NI go to the doctor,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.53,0:58:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to\Ngive them a number
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.95,0:59:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,because they already know\Nwho I am through my device.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.58,0:59:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So I won't have to provide\Na social security number.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.06,0:59:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So I think that's the good part.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.80,0:59:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But I do believe that cyber,\Nup until this point in time,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.44,0:59:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,has been used for financial\Ncrimes or gathering
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.20,0:59:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,data and information\Nwhich is of value.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.81,0:59:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going to happen is we're\Ngoing to see cyber very quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.53,0:59:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,now turn very black.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.93,0:59:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have the ability,\Nas you know, to basically
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.50,0:59:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,shut someone's pacemaker off.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.59,0:59:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But we have to be\Nwithin 35 feet of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.52,0:59:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We test these device at\NQuantico all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.22,0:59:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So as long as I walk up\Nwithin 35 feet of you,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.46,0:59:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I take control of any bodily\Ndevice you have on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.55,0:59:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I want to\Nassassinate you, I
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.38,0:59:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,want to speed it up, take\Nit down, I can do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.50,0:59:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But I believe that\Nin five years,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.36,0:59:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll be able to do that\Nfrom 5,000 miles away.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.35,0:59:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We have the ability\Nnow that we test
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.22,0:59:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that we can chase a car\Ndown the interstate.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.31,0:59:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got to get up within\N35 feet of the vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.74,0:59:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We take over the vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.48,1:00:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We shut the motor off.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.04,1:00:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We lock the person in the car.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.57,1:00:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We lock the power window\Nso they can't open them.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.19,1:00:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We can turn on their airbag.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.22,1:00:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, five years\Nfrom now, you'd
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.11,1:00:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,be able to do that\N5,000 miles away.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.56,1:00:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So yeah, so our electrical\Ngrid uses as a terrorist tool.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.95,1:00:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The ability to shut\Ndown an entire system,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.38,1:00:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,shut down an entire\Nbanking system.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.90,1:00:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are all the things\Nthat, unfortunately, we'll
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.24,1:00:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,be dealing with in the next four\Nor five years as cyber starts
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.20,1:00:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to make that turn to the\Nvery black side of cyber,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.03,1:00:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,not just about stealing\Nmoney, information, and data.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.32,1:00:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that's why we're going\Nto have to work extra hard
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.19,1:00:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to make sure that we go back\Nto protect our electrical grid.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.77,1:00:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I always remind people\Nwe have the technology
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.94,1:00:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to prevent most\Nof these problems.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.56,1:00:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you don't use\Nit, then it's worthless.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.13,1:00:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And we tend to develop\Na lot of things--
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.20,1:00:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want to make\Nthis emphasis to you--
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.95,1:00:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,we develop a lot of things\Nwithout following them through.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.53,1:00:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So one thing I've\Ndone in the government
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.23,1:01:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,over the last several years,\Nif the government is going
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.52,1:01:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to buy a technology, they send\Nme to the technology company
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.27,1:01:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and say, try to defeat that.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.40,1:01:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I just simply go there\Nand see their technology.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.77,1:01:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,As one CEO says, he\Nplays chess with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.81,1:01:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You tell him you did\Nthis, this, and this.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.69,1:01:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he tells you,\Nwe have a weakness right
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.65,1:01:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,here because I would\Ncome in and do this.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.81,1:01:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So they build a wall up.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.86,1:01:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he says, no, I\Nwould still get in here
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.20,1:01:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,until he says he can't\Ndo it any longer.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.06,1:01:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we know we have\Na good technology.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.27,1:01:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But very rarely is--
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.12,1:01:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and I did that with\NTrusona when we did it
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.02,1:01:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,for the purpose of the CIA.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.88,1:01:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But today-- and it\Ntells you on the website
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.66,1:01:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that I advised on\Ntheir project and how
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.22,1:01:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,it came down to commercial use.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.25,1:01:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But today, what we have\Nis we develop things.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.26,1:01:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So we say to you, here's a\Ndevice you put in your kitchen,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.68,1:01:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you can talk to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.85,1:01:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You ask what the weather\Nis, what's on TV tonight,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.09,1:01:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,all of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.19,1:01:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I could easily reverse that\Nand listen to everything
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.36,1:01:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you say in your house.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.74,1:01:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There are so many\Nweaknesses in your home.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.91,1:01:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Your security cameras are access\Npoints, your remote control
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.53,1:02:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,on your TV, your\NSamsung television,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.32,1:02:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,your refrigerator that tells\Nyou how much milk is in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.19,1:02:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,My thing is I really\Ndon't need my refrigerator
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.86,1:02:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to talk to my toaster.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.35,1:02:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They've gotten along\Nfor a long time
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.86,1:02:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,without ever having\Na conversation.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.33,1:02:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But what happens is\Nwe develop something.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.36,1:02:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We get really excited about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.65,1:02:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,"We gotta get this\Nto the marketplace."
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.45,1:02:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And sure enough, we never\Nlook at the negative side.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.69,1:02:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All I try to say to technology\Ncompany, yeah, this is great.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.32,1:02:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, can you take a\Nlittle time to just
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.06,1:02:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,say, how would someone\Nuse this technology
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.42,1:02:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,in a negative, self-serving\Nway so that we build
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.93,1:02:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the block to that\Nbefore we ever give it
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.24,1:02:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to the public to use it?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.18,1:02:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd save a lot of problems.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.96,1:02:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Been an absolute pleasure\Nspending the morning with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.67,1:02:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much for coming.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.84,1:02:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.72,1:02:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.94,1:02:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
